message.content: OpenAI is an artificial intelligence research organization that aims to build and promote safe, beneficial AI. It produces state-of-the-art AI models, conducts research on various AI techniques, and develops technologies to ensure the responsible deployment of AI systems. OpenAI also actively contributes to the development of open-source tools and frameworks for the AI community.

message.content: OpenAI was founded by Elon Musk, Sam Altman, Greg Brockman, Ilya Sutskever, John Schulman, and Wojciech Zaremba. However, Elon Musk is no longer directly involved with the organization. Today, OpenAI is governed by a board of directors and is made up of a team of researchers and engineers working towards their mission of advancing artificial intelligence in a safe and beneficial way.
